## Plan
1. Import `io` and `net/http` packages.
2. Use `io.ReadAll` to read from `r.Body`.
3. Handle potential read errors.
4. Convert result to string and return.

## Solution
```go
import (
    "io"
    "net/http"
)

func readBody(r *http.Request) (string, error) {
    body, err := io.ReadAll(r.Body)
    if err != nil {
        return "", err
    }
    return string(body), nil
}
```
